betterquesting:10.desc:8: A Crook will increase the chance of getting Saplings from Leaves.
To make the various machines in the Plastic Age, you are going to need a Polyethylene Hulls and Plastic.

Welcome to GregBlock! To begin with the Manual Age you are going to need to get 2 Logs from the tree on your island and make a Crafting Table. Yup, 2. This, my friend, is GregTech.

 If you're playing on multiplayer and want to join someone else, do /island for information on how to do that.
To start with the Steam Age, you are going to need a Small Steam Coal Boiler. It uses fuel to create heat to turn Water into Steam. It automatically transfers Steam to adjacent machines.
You're able to obtain Water by melting Leaves, Saplings or Cacti in a Wooden Crucible, or by collecting Water with a Barrel.

In order to get into the LV Age, you are going to need to make your very first Basic Circuit. In order to make it, you are going to need 3 Red Alloy Cables, 2 Vacuum Tubes, 2 Resistors, which are made with Paper, Coal Dust and regular or Fine Copper Wires, a Steel Plate and the Coated Circuit Board you made earlier. To make Red Alloy Cables, you are going to need to make Red Alloy, an alloy of Redstone and Copper, make Wires and then insulate them with Black Carpet.
Getting to the MV Age is not too much more complicated than gettng to the LV Age was. You're going to need a Good Electronic Circuit, which is made with 4 Basic Circuits and a Diode.

Now that you have advanced Circuits, all that's left for getting into the HV Age is the Machine Hull. To make one, you are going to need Stainless Steel, an alloy of Iron, Nickel, Chrome and Manganese.

Since you already have an exteme Circuit, all that's left for you to get into the EV age is the Machine Hull. It's made out of Titanium, which can siply be made by putting together the Titanium Tetrachloride and Manganese in the Electric Blast Furnace and then freezing it.
Once again, you have the Circuits and now all that's left for getting to the next tier is the Hull. To make the IV one, you are going to need Tungstensteel.

As always, now that you have master Circuits, all that's left for getting into the LuV Age is the Machine Hull. However, this time it isn't the main material that you're missing, it's the Cables. You are going to need Vanadium-Gallium Cables.
By putting Saplings, Apples, Silk Worms, Leaves, Rotten Flesh and similar items into a Barrel and waiting a while, you are able to make yourself more Dirt.
Now that you have the Circuits, with some Osmium and Naquadah Alloy, you'll be able to make the UV Machine Hull and get into the UV Age.
While using your Crook on Leaves, you are able to obtain a Silk Worm. You can then infest Leaves with it to obtain String.
A Sieve with a String Mesh will allow you to sift a variety of materials, including Dirt. By sifting Dirt, you ca obtain Pebbles, with which you can craft Cobblestone.

You are able to smelt an Iron Nugget into a Wrough Iron one and then craft 9 of those into a Wrough Iron Ingot. Wrough Iron can be used for most things that regular Iron can be used for, but the tools made from it have 1.5 times the durability.
By putting Dust into a Barrel or Wooden Crucible filled with Water, you are able to make Clay.
With some Coblestone, you are able to make a Stone Hammer. With it, you are able to turn Cobblestone into Gravel, Gravel into Sand and Sand into Dust.
As in vanilla Minecraft, with 8 Cobblestone you are able to make a simple Furnace. You should probably make more than one though.
With some Clay, you'll be able to make a Clay Bucket for carrying around fluids. However, if the fluid is too hot, the Bucket will break upon placing it.
With some wood, you are able to make a simple mob farm. Simply make a dark room 25-40 blocks away from your base.

With a Porcelain Crucible you'll be able to melt Cobblestone and similar materials into Lava. For that to happen, you are going to need a heat source, such as a Torch, below it. Then, using a Bucket, you are able to collect it, place it in the world and make a manual Cobblestone generator.

By Siftng Gravel and Sand, you are able to obtain Ore Chunks of which some can be smelted into Ingots. With the String Mesh, the main materials you are going to get are Iron, Tin, Copper, Coal and Lignite. There's also Gold, but that's a bit rare.

Note: Copper is most common from Sand.

For carrying around fluids, you are going to need a Bucket. Now, you know how a Bucket is Curved? Well, to make it you are going to need to curve some Plates with a Bending Cylinder. Sure, you could have also made a Clay Bucket, but that doesnt quite work on hot fluids, so you're better off making an Iron one.

With a bit of Iron, you are able to make a simple machine that produce Cobblestone in a single block space. It does not however auto-output, so you'll need to use Hoppers or other forms of piping. The speed at which you get it pretty much depends on how fast you can pipe it out.

Note: As all other machines that consume tools in their recipes, you specifically need Iron tools.
When working with hot fluids, Clay isn't gonna cut it. You are going to need a Porcelain; a combination of Clay and Bone Meal. To turn Bones into Bone Meal, you are going to need a Mortar.
You don't have access to Ducts, but you have access to the next best thing; Channels!
You can't make Ducts yet, so it's time for the next best thing: Hoppers! I'm not talking about your laggy, one-input-sided, non-filtered vanilla Hopper, I'm talking about the next level Hopper!

In order to progress to the next age, you are going to need Bronze. To make it, you are going to need to mix Copper and Tin Dust. But hold up, you are first going to need a Mortar to turn the Ingots into Dusts.

In order to progress to tier 3 resources, you are going to need Steel, which is made from Iron and Coal, Charcoal or Coal Coke in a Primitive Blast Furnace. To make one, you are in theory just going to need a lot of Clay, 144 to be exact. You are first going to need to turn Bricks into Brick Dust and Clay into Clay Dust, combine them to make Fireclay Dust, compress it, smelt it and then craft 4 of the Bricks you made into Primitive Bricks.
The Tin Alloy Mesh gives you access to a range of new materials, including Redstone, Cobalt and Certus Quartz.

It would be a good idea to use the Grass Seeds you got from sifting Dirt to make a small Grass area in middle of your island, where you have a Plains biome. You can then set Baits to spawn specific animals. A Cow is one mob that you will need to progress. You can also quite simply automate collecting Milk from it by placing it on top of a Barrel.

While sifting Dirt, you are able to obtain Ancient Spores. When right-clicking Dirt with them it gets turned into Mycelium. However, to make use of this Mycelium, you are going to need to have a 3x3 area of it and place a Barrel filled with Water on the middle block. Mushrooms will start growing and the Water will slowly turn into Witch Water.

With an Auto Sifter and a few Water Wheels, you are able to harness the kinetic energy of Water to automatically sift. The Auto Sifter can connect to a 5x5 of Sieves above it and automatically puts what's piped into it into them. The more Water Wheels connected, the faster it will go. However, to make all of this you are going to need Stone Gears and for them you are going to need a Screwdriver.

By mixing Lava and Redstone, you are able to make Netherrack. Just as Cobblestone, it can be crushed and then sifted. While sifting Crushed Netherrack, you'll obtain many materials you'd obtain from sifting Gravel or Sand, but you'll also obtain Sulfur, Nether Quartz and Zinc.
The Extractor, as the name suggests, allows you to extract certain materials from items, mainly Dyes. It can do recipes that require up to 16EU/t.
With a Saw you'll be able to get 4 Planks from your Logs and 4 Sticks from your Planks. However, to make it, you are first going to need a File.

The Steam Macerator is used for turning items and blocks into the corresponding Dusts. While the electric ones can double Ore outputs, the Steam one cannot and has only one output slot. It can do recipes that require up to 16EU/t.
With 6 Ingots and a Stick you are able to make a much faster Hammer. It also allows you to make Plates. Plates are needed for almost everything in GregTech.

The Steam Turbine can turn Steam into power. To make it, you are going to need Motors, which need Magnetic Iron Rods, made by crafting together an Iron Rod and 4 Redstone, and Tin Cables. As all other LV machines, it also requires an LV Machine Hull.
The Alloy Smelter, as the name suggest, allows you to automatically make alloys. It can do recipes that require up to 16EU/t.

The Forge Hammer is an automatic Hammer, allowing you to automatically make Plates, crush Cobble, Gravel, Sand, etc. and crush down Ores, which you will later be able to process to get more materials from them. It can do recipes that require up to 16EU/t.
The High Pressure Steam Coal Boiler produces Steam faster than the regular one.
The High Pressure Steam Furnace is faster than the regular one.
The Steam Compressor is used for compressing various items, mainly for turning Ingots into Blocks. It can do recipes that require up to 16EU/t.
The High Pressure Steam Macerator is the same as the regular one, but it can do recipes that require up to 32EU/t.
The Steam Furnace lets you smelt items with Steam.
As the name suggests, the Steam Lava Boiler uses Lava instead of fuel to create heat.

Some metals can't simply be smelted in a Furnace and require an Electric Blast Furnace to be processed into Ingots. The EBF can accept different Coils that give it different maximum temperatures. Different metals are going to need different temperatures. For certain recipes, in this case Aluminium, you are going to need multiple Energy Input Hatches in order to reach the needed voltage. Once you have items in it and power connected to it, it will start working. To make the simplest one, you are going to need 2 new alloys: Invar and Cupronickel. As you progress, you'll be able to make better and better Coils.
With the Steel Mesh, you are now able to obtain tier 3 resources, including Emeralds, Lapis, Lead, Silver, Thorium and Uranium.
The High Pressure Steam Extractor does the same as the regular one, but it can do recipes that require up to 32EU/t.

With some Wood Planks ,made by compressing Wood Pulp, and some Sticky Resin, made by smelting Slime Balls, you are able to make a Basic Circuit Board used for crafting the most basic Basic Circuit. To obtain Slime, you can combine Milk and Mushrooms in a Barrel.
The High Pressure Steam Forge Hammer does the same as the regular one, but it can do recipes that require up to 32EU/t.
The High Pressure Steam Alloy Smelter does the same as the regular one, but it can do recipes that require up to 32EU/t.
The High Pressure Steam Lava Boiler is faster than the regular one.
The High Pressure Steam Compressor does the same as the regular one, but it can do recipes that require up to 32EU/t.
With the Aluminium Mesh, you are now have access to the last tier of resources. However, you still don't have everything.
The Basic Extractor uses LV power to extract materials from certain items.
The Basic Electrolyzer uses LV power to separate certain fluids and dusts.

The Basic Arc Furnace uses Oxygen and LV power to turn metal parts into Ingots and Nuggets. However, it comes at a cost. Rubber, Wood and plastics get turned into Ash, Copper gets turned into Annealed Copper and Iron gets turned into Wrought Iron. Before you can make one, you are going to need Graphite.
The Basic Autoclave uses Water and LV power to turn gem dusts into the corresponding gems.
The Basic Alloy Smelter uses LV power to create alloys.
The Basic Cluster Mill uses LV power to turn Plates into Foils.
The Basic Bending Machine uses LV power to turn Ingots into Plates and Plates into Curved or Dense Plates.
The Basic Chemical Reactor uses LV power to combine items and fluids.
The Basic Centrifuge uses LV power to separate certain items, mainly Ore dusts.
The Basic Assembling Machine uses LV power to auto-craft items that take 3 different materials, however, its main purpose is making Cables.
The Basic Electric Furnace uses LV power to smelt items.
The Basic Wiremill uses LV power to turn Ingots into Wires.
The Basic Mixer uses LV power to create alloy Dusts.
The Basic Fluid Extractor uses LV power to turn metal items and items of similar materials into fluids.
The Basic Fluid Canner uses LV power to fill up fluid containers.
The Basic Fluid Heater uses LV power to heat up certain fluids.
The Basic Fluid Solidifier uses LV power to mold liquid metals.
The Basic Unpackager uses LV power to disassemble Cables and uncraft items in a 3x3.
The Basic Packager uses LV power to automatically insulate ULV and LV Wires and autocraft Tiny and Small Piles of Dusts into full Dusts.
The Basic Chemical Bath uses LV power and certain fluids to purify Crushed Ores, undye blocks and make some other items.
The Basic Polzarizer uses LV power to turn Iron, Steel and Neodynium into their magnetic versions.
The Basic Distillery uses LV power to distill certain liquids, mainly Oil. However, you don't have good access to Oil right now.
The Basic Macerator uses LV power to double the Ore output and crush down items.
The Basic Ore Washing Plant uses LV power and Water to purify Crushed Ores.
The Basic Forge Hammer uses LV power to crush Ores and make Plates.

The Large Bronze Boiler is a multblock structure that is able to create a much larger amount of Steam than the single-block Boilers. It uses Furnace, Diesel Generator and SemiFluid fuels to heat up. As it heats up, it produces more and more Steam. Once it's at max heat, it starts using less fuel. Furnace fuels last a 60th of the amount they do in a Furnace, Diesel Generator fuels last a quarter the amount they do in the Diesel Generator and SemiFluid fuels last double the amount displayed in JEI.
The Basic Thermal Centrifuge uses LV power to centrifuge Crushed and Purified Ores.

Lubricant is the most efficient lubricant in the Cuttng Machine and is used in almost all Assembly Line recipes (thought you're really far from making that multiblock). Even thought it can be made in the Distillery, it's most efficiently made in the Mixer, bu combining Oil, Seed Oil or Creosote Oil with Talc, Soapstone or Redstone Dust.
The Basic Sifting Machine uses LV power to sift Purified gem Ores in the hopes of getting a better gem. To make it, you're first going to need 2 Item Filter.

The Basic Cutting Saw uses LV power and Water or Lubricant to cut metal Blocks into 9 Plates, Long Rods into 2 Rods, Rods into 4 Bolts and Screws into Bolts. To make it, you're first going to need a Diamond Sawblade made from Diamond Dust and Cobalt Brass.
By combining Raw Rubber, extracted from Slime Balls or Sticky Resin, and Sulfur, you are able to make molten Rubber. With the Fluid Solidifier you can then cast it into any usable shape you want.
The Basic Lathe uses LV power to turn Ingots and gems into Rods, Bolts into Screws and gem Plates into Lenses.
The Basic Microwave uses LV power to cook food. It uses less power than the Electric Furnace, but you don't want to put anything that isn't food in it.
You are able to make better Chests and Tanks with the major GregTech materials, the first one of those being Bronze.
By sifting Dust with the Steel Mesh, you can obtain Glowstone, Blaze Powder and Sky Stone Dust.

By throwing a Blazing Doll into a Stone Barrel filled with Lava, you'll be able to summon a Blaze. To make that Doll, you are going to need a Nether Wart, obtained by sifting Soul Sand. Soul Sand can be made by putting Sand in a Barrel filled with Witch Water.

The LV Battery Buffers allow you to store LV power in Batteries. There are different Batteries with different power capacities and there are different Buffers with diffrent storage capacities. It's generally a good idea to store your power so you don't use it up at the same time you're generating it. Before making any Batteries, you are going to need Battery Alloy, made from Lead and Antimony.
The MV Battery Buffers allow you to store MV power in Batteries.
The Basic Canning Machine uses LV power to fill up certain items with certain materials.
With Plastic, you are able to make Conveyors that move items in the world. They can even insert into or export out of chests and machines.

As you may have noticed, you can't craft Wooden tools. However, you can make Flint tools from GregTech. All of GregTech's tools aren't in JEI, only the Darmstandium versions are. However, you can click on them to view the recipes for all the versions of said tools. Unlike the rest of the GT Tools, the Flint ones can be crafted the vanilla way.
The Basic Gas Turbine uses gases and some liquids to generate LV power. It so happens that Hydrogen is one of them.

The Advanced Wiremill uses MV power to turn Ingots into Wires.

The Advanced Precision Laser Engraver uses MV power and Lenses to engrave and etch certain items.
With a Medium Voltage Transformer you are able to switch between LV and MV power.
The Petrofied Generator uses fuel to generate RF.
Instead of using Wands, you can use a Building Gadget. While it does use RF, it has many different options.
Using an Animal Sewer, you can collect Sewage from the mobs above it and using a Sewage Composter, you can turn it into Fertilizer.
The Mob Crusher uses power to kill mobs in front of it and automatically collects their drops and experience, in the form of Essence.
The Energy Fied Provider can wirelessly transfer RF to machines linked to it via Field Addons.

Industrial Foregoing provides you with all the machines you'd need for an automatic snimal farm: a Grower that makes them grow faster, a Rancher that milks cows and shears Sheep, a Feeder that automatically feeds them, a Baby Separator that separates the babies from the adults and a Slaughter Factory that automatically slaughters them.
You are able to make a Block Breaker and Placer that just use a bit of power to work.
The Lava Fabricator uses 200RF to generate Lava.

Industrial Foregoing has everything needed for automating a crop farm: a Hydrator for keeping the Farland moist, a Sower for placing crops, a Fertilizer for aplplying Bonemeal or Fertilizer and a Gatherer for harvesting the crops.
When the Plant Gatherer cuts down trees, it creates Sludge. With a Sludge Refiner, you can turn that sludge into somewhat useful items.
The Bioreactor is able to turn Seeds and Saplings into Biofuel, which can be used in the Biofuel Generator for RF.
The Mob Duplicator uses Mob Essence and RF to duplicate the mob captured in the Imprisonment Tool stored in it.
With the Protein Reactor you can turn meat into Protein, which can be used in the Protein Generator for RF.
A Meat Feeder filled with Liquid Meat will automatically feed you when in your inventory.
With a Microprocessor you're able to upgrade your Building Gadget into an Exchange one, allowing you to exchange blocks on your island for other ones.

To get into the Digital Age, you are going to need Fluix Crystals. They are made by mixing together Nether Quartz, Redstone and Charged Certus Quartz in Water. Charged Certus Quartz is made by electrolyzing Certus Quartz.
For making AE2 Circuits, you are going to need Presses. They can be made by engraving Dense Tantalum Plates. Tantalum is obtained by electrolyzing Tantalite.
The Basic Forming Press uses LV power to press certain items.
Most AE2 machines can't directly use RF and need AE power. With a Power Acceptor, you can turn RF into AE power. To Transfer it, you are going to need Cables.

You are able to use the Presses, you made, in a Forming Press to make AE2 Circuits and with them Prcessors. However, you are first going to need Silicon. Silicon is obtained by electrolyzing Redstone, Clay and other materials.
You are now able to make an ME Chest and 1K Storage Cell for digitally storing items!

Now that you have a basic ME system, you should start automating with it. It's quite simple to do that. First off, for anything to actually be made, you are going to need a Crafting Processor and Patterns. You can set recipe Patterns with a Pattern Terminal. Then place Interfaces next to your machines and put the Patterns in them.
It would be a good idea to add a Crafting Terminal to your ME system so you don't have to switch between ME Chests and Crafting Tables.

The Glass Cables can only transfer 8 channels which isn't so good for your small ME system. Luckily, you are able to make better Cables. These are the Smart Cables, that transfer 16 channels and the Dense Smart Cables that transfer 32 chaneels, but can't connect to anything but other Cables. To make both of them, you are first going to need Covered Cables.

Instead of making recipes on request, you can simply automatically import/export things from your ME system. You can also use a Storage Bus to store things you don't want clogging up your ME system in another storage container, but still have easy access to it.

The Multi Smelter is a multiblock structure that allows you to smelt multiple items at a time using power. The amount of items it can smelt at a time depends on the Coils it has.
The Pyrolyse Oven is a multiblock that allows you to turn Logs into Charcoal and obtain many different more or less useful fluids in the process.

While with the Energy Acceptors you can theoretically have as many interlinking systems as you'd like, to have them work as one single system, you are going to need ME Controllers. To make them, you are going to need Quantum Entangled Singularities, made by exploding regular Singularities together with Ender Dust. You can make a regular Singularity by shoving 256000 items in a Matter Condenser.

There are some things that simply can't be made in machines, so you are going to need to autocraft them. The only way of autocrafting things in this pack is with a Molecular Assembler. To make one, you are first going to need to kill 9 Withers, make a Nether Star Block, cut it into Plates and turn them into Lenses.
A Security Terminal will let you configure who can access your ME system.
You are able to add a Wireless Access Point to your ME system to alllow wireless access to it. You are then able to link a Wireless Crafting Terminal to it by putting it in your Security Terminal.
The Implosion Compressor is a 3x3x3 multiblock that uses explosives to turn gem Dusts back into gems.
The Large Steel Boiler can reach higher temperatures and a higher maximum amount of mb/t, but is less fuel efficient.
When making certain materials in the Industrial Blast Furnace, they turn into Hot Ingots. In order to cool them down, you are going to need a multiblock Vacuum Freezer.
For making Titanium and higher tier metals, you are going to need more heat in your Industrial Blast Furnace, meaning it's finally time to upgrade your Cupronickel Coils with Kanthal ones.

Titanium Tetrachloride is needed for making Titanium and can also be used for increasing the yield of your polymeres. To make it, you're first going to need to electrolyze 39 Bauxite Dust, one of the first materials you obtain, to get Rutile Dust, which you can then combine with Carbon and Chlorine.

The Advanced Brewery III uses EV power to automatically brew Potions.
The Advanced Mixer III uses EV power to create alloy Dusts.
The Advanced Packager III uses EV power to insulate  ULV and LV Wires and autocraft Tiny and Small Piles of Dusts into full Dusts.
The Advanced Fluid Heater III uses EV power to heat up certain fluids.
The Advanced Chemical Bath III uses Sodium Persulfide and EV power to purify Crushed Ores. It can also undye Glass, Clay and Wood with Chlorine.
The Advanced Assembling Machine III uses EV power to auto-craft items that take 3 different materials, however, its main purpose is making Cables.
The Advanced Bending Machine III uses EV power to turn Ingots into Plates and Plates into Curved or Dense Plates.
The Advanced Sifting Machine III uses EV power to sift Purified gem Oes in the hopes of getting a better gem.
The Advanced Autoclave III uses Water and EV power to turn gem dusts into the corresponding gems.
The Advanced Ore Washing Plant III uses EV power and Water to purify Crushed Ores.
The Advanced Fluid Solidifier III uses EV power to mold liquid metals.
The Advanced Microwave III uses EV power to cook food. It uses less power than the Electric Furnace, but you don't want to put anything that isn't food in it.
The Advanced Cutting Saw III uses EV power and Water or Lubricant to cut metal Blocks into 9 Plates, Long Rods into 2 Rods, Rods into 4 Bolts and Screws into Bolts.
The Advanced Extractor III uses EV power to extract materials from certain items.
The Advanced Precision Laser Engraver III uses EV power and Lenses to engrave and etch certain items.
The Advanced Unpackager III uses EV power to disassemble Cables and uncraft items in a 3x3.
The Advanced Lathe III uses EV power to turn Ingots and gems into Rods, Bolts into Screws and gem Plates into Lenses.
The Turbo Fluid Canner uses EV power to fill up fluid containers.
The Basic Compressor uses LV power to compress various items. It's mainly used for automatically turning Ingots, gems and Dusts into Blocks.
The Advanced Compressor uses MV power to compress various items. It's mainly used for automatically turning Ingots, Dusts and gems into Blocks.
The Advanced Compressor II uses HV power to compress various items. It's mainly used for automatically turning gems, Ingots and Dusts into Blocks.
The Advanced Compressor III uses EV power to compress various items. It's mainly used for automatically turning gems, Dusts and Ingots into Blocks.
The Cracking Unit is a multiblock that's specialized in turning Oil products into their Steam and Hydro-Cracked versions.
By having Water between y-level 60 and 45, you can have Squids spawn. Whether you have a pool where you manually kill them or a waterfall that leads to their demise is all up to you.
Before you are able to make any type of Bricks, you are going to need Forms to form the corresponding types of Clay into the corresponding types of Unfired Bricks.
With a multiblock Coke Oven you'll be able to turn Logs into Charcoal, Coal into Coal Coke and Lignite into Lignite Coke, which are much better fuels.

Now that you have Steel, you are able to make a primitive circuit, a Vacuum Tube. It's used for making, get this, only one machine! And you know what's even better? -You'll probably never make it! It's also used for making the most basic Basic Circuit, but those are just small details. Anyways, to make one of these bad boys yourself, you are going to need a Glass Tube, some Paper and regular or Fine Copper Wires. The Glass Tube is made with a Ball Mold and Glass Dust in an Alloy Smelter, Paper can be made in two ways, either with Wood Pulp and Water or Chad and Stone Slabs, and for making the Wires you are going to need a Wire Cutter.

With Whichwater you are able to turn Skeletons into Wither Skeletons and Sand into Soul Sand, meaning you can now summn a Wither and kill it to obtain a Nether Star (and probably die in the process).

Note: This quest is a bit of a troll quest as you don't actually need to kill the Wither until MV at the earliest.

Now that you have Silver, you are able to make Solar Boilers. As you could probably guess, they are used to passively produce Steam, as long as its daytime. During the night, the heat it has will decrease and it will stop working. This one only comes in a Bronze form as otherwise it'd be overpowered.
The Steam Pump uses Steam to collect fluids, mainly Water, every 6s. Unlike the rest of the Steam machines, it has an output instead of an exhaust.
The LV Electric Pump is a common crafting components for LV machines that use fluids.
The LV Emitter is a crafting component for a few LV machines. Before you can make one, you are going to need to make a new alloy: Brass. It's an alloy of Copper and Zinc.
The LV Conveyor Module is simply used for crafting a few LV machines.
The Basic Circuit Assembling Machine Uses LV power to automatically create Circuits and similar items.
The Basic Electromagnetic Separator uses LV power to separate Pure Dusts which contain magnetic elements.
For more compact forced outputting, you can use Servos.
The LV Electric Piston is used for making several LV machines related to extracting and/or crushing.
The LV Robot Arm is used for crafting a few machines, 2 of wihich are some of the most important for progression.
The Basic Pump uses LV power to suck up fluids every 3s. The one you're probably need sucked up is Water.
One of the simplest things you can electrolyze is Water. As you could have probably guessed, that will give you Oxygen and Hydrogen, which are some of the most used elements in machine recipes.
Gallium is a resource commonly used in making crafting components for Circuits. However, it's not a material that has its own Ore. It can be obtained by electrolyzing Sphalerite.

Wafers are used for making common Circuit components such as CPUs and RAM. They're made by cutting Silicon Boules, which are made in an Electric Blast Furnace with Silicon and Gallium. Silicon can be obtained by electrolyzing a variety of Dusts, including Clay and Redstone.
The Advanced Air Collector uses MV power to collect 2 buckets of Air every second.
For making Circuits, Rotors and parts in the Assembling Machine, you are going to need a certain soldering fluid. The best one is Soldering Alloy, an alloy of Tin and Antimony.
The Advanced Circuit Assembling Machine uses MV power to assemble Circuits.
The Advanced Canning Machine uses MV power to fill up certain items with other materials.
The MV Electric Pump is a common crafting components for MV machines that use fluids.
The MV Conveyor Module is simply used for crafting a few MV machines.
The MV Electric Piston is used for making several MV machines related to extracting and/or crushing.
The MV Emitter is a crafting component for a few MV machines. Before you can make one, you are going to need to make a new alloy: Electrum. It's an alloy of Gold and Silver.
The MV Robot Arm is used for crafting a few MV machines, 2 of wihich are some of the most important for progression.
The Advanced Pump uses MV power to collect Water every 1.5s.
With the Advanced Distillery, you are now able to distill Biomass into Ethanol. Biomass is made by combining plant-related items and Water in the Brewery.
The Fermenter is a machine that has pretty much one job: fermenting Biomass. Fermented Biomass has more possible outputs than regular Biomass and requires less power to be distilled.

One of the fluids you get from pyrolysing Logs is literally called "Charcoal Byproducts". It can be distilled into Wood Vinegar, Gas and Tar, which you can also obtain as separate byproducts from pyrolysing Logs. They can then be distilled again for obtaining some useful fluids.
The Ethylene is a fluid commonly used for making polymeres and rubbers. It can be obtained by either reacting Ethanol and Sulfuric Acid or by distilling one of the many Steam-Cracked outputs of Oil.
No Description
Polyethylene is one of the simplest and mostly commonly used polymeres. It's made by combining Ehylene with Air or Oxygen, with the latter giving you a better output.

Silicone Rubber can be used as a substitute for regular Rubber in a few recipes and you need 2 times less of it for making Cables than you would need regular Rubber. You can take many different paths to making it.
Polystyrene is a polymere made by combining Styrene with Air or Oxygen. Styrene itself is made with Benzene and Ethylene.

Another thing you can make with that Styrene is a type of Rubber. Styrene-Butadiene Rubber can be used as a substitute for regular Rubber in some recipes and you need 1.5 times less of it for making Cables. As you could have imagined, it's made with Styrene and Butadiene.

Instead of centrifuging Sticky Resin, you can use a combination of Polyvinyl Acetate and Acetone or Methyl Acetate for making Glue. Polyvinyl Acetate is a polymere, so it's made with Vinyl Acetate and Air or Oxygen. Vynil Acetate is made with Oxygen, Acetic Acid and Ethylene.
Polyvinyl Chloride is a not so commonly used polymere made by combining Vinyl Chloride with Oxygen or Air.
Instead of using Sticky Resin, you are now able to create Raw Rubber artificially, with Isoprene. It can be made with just Propene or a combination of Propene and Ethylene.

With the Laser Engraver you'll be able to make your Wafers into Wafers for usable components and then cut them into said components. As previously stated, the ones you can make with the regular Silicon Wafer are the Integrate Circuit, RAM and CPU.
The Integrated Logic Circuit is a basic Circuit that can be made automatically. To make one, you are going to need a Phenolic Circuit Board.
The Integrated Processor is a good Circuit. To make one you are going to need a Plastic Circuit Board.
The Processor Assembly is an upgrade from the Integrated Processor. It's a advanced Circuit.
The Good Integrated Circuit is an upgrade from the Integrated Logic Circuit. It's an automatable good Circuit.
The regular Advanced Circuit is an upgrade from the Good Integrated Circuit. As you could have probably guessed, it's an advanced Circuit.

The Microprocessor is probably the best basic Circuit as long as you have all the components produced at a decent rate. You get 4 per recipe and to make them you are going to need a Plastic Circuit Board.

Bisphenol A can be used for making a few Circuit components. It's made with Phenol, Acetone and Hydrochloric Acid. While there multiple ways to make Phenol, the most efficient way is with Oxygen and Cumene, which can be made with Benzene, Phosphoric Acid and Propene.
No Description
The Advanced Electromagnetic Separator uses MV power to separate Pure Dusts that contain magnetic elements.
The Advanced Canning Machine II uses HV power to fill certain items with certain materials.
The Advanced Circuit Assembling Machine II uses HV power to assemble Circuits.
The Advanced Electromagnetic Separator II uses HV power to separate Pure Dusts that contain magnetic elements.
The Advanced Fermenter II uses HV power to ferment Biomass.
The HV Emitter is a crafting component for a few HV machines.
The HV Electric Piston is used for making several HV machines related to extracting and/or crushing.
The HV Conveyor Module is simply used for crafting a few HV machines.
The HV Electric Pump is a common crafting components for HV machines that use fluids.
The HV Robot Arm is used for crafting a few HV machines, 2 of wihich are some of the most important for progression.

Polytetrafluoroethylene is a really strong polymere used in many late-game recipes. It's made with Tetrafluoroethylene and Air or Oxygen. Tetrafluoroethylene is made with Chloroform and Hydrofluoric Acid.
The Workstation is an upgrade from the Processor Assembly. It's an extreme Circuit.
The regular Mainframe is an upgrade from the Workstation. It's an elite Circuit.
The Advanced Pump II uses HV power to collect Water every second.
Bio Diesel is a good fuel that can be made by reacting Methanol or Ethanol with Seed or Fish Oil.

Cetane-Boosted Diesel is the best Diesel Generator Fuel. It can be made with a bit of Tetranitromethane and Diesel, Light Fuel or Bio Diesel, all giving different outputs. Tetranitromethane is made with Ethenone and Nitric Acid.
Diesel is a good fuel made by mixing Heavy and Light Fuel.
Instead of by killing Spiders, you can obtain String from Polycaprolactam. Unlike the other polymeres, this one is made with Naphtha and Saltpeter, which is obtained by centrifuging Soul Sand.
Roket Fuel is a really good Gas Turbine fuel and making it the less efficient way only requires Air and Water, which you have infinite amounts of.
For making Osmium, Tungstensteel and other metals in the Electric Blast Furnace, you are going to need to upgrade your Kanthal Coils to Nichrome ones.

Your Electric Blast Furnace can now reach the correct temperature for making Osmium. Osmium is used for making Field Generators, which are used for making Mass Fabricators, Replicators and Naquadah Reactors. T obtain the Dust, you are going to need to thermal centrifuge Iridium Ore.
End Stone can be made by combining Glowstone Dust and Deuterium in a Barrel.
Just as Netherrack, you are able to crush End Stone to be able to sift it. From End Stone you'll be able to get the last 2 Ores you've been missing: Naquadah and Enriched Naquadah.

The Large Steam Turbine is a multiblock version of the regular Steam Turbine, that also gives you back Water. While you can make it in HV, you're mainly going to need it after HV as the regular Turbines only go up to HV.
The Large Gas Turbine is a multiblock version of the regular Gas Turbine.
The Advanced Fermenter III uses EV power to ferment Biomass.
The Advanced Pump III uses EV power to collect Water every 3/4 of a second.
The Advanced Circuit Assembling Machine III uses EV power to assemble circuits.
The Advanced Mass Fabricator III uses EV power to turn dusts and fluids into Positive and Neutral Matter.
The Advanced Replicator III uses EV power and Positive and Neutral Matter to replicate materials.
The Advanced Canning Machine III uses EV power to fill certain items with certain materials.
The EV Electric Pump is a common crafting components for EV machines that use fluids.
The EV Conveyor Module is simply used for crafting a few EV machines.
The HV Electric Piston is used for making several HV machines related to extracting and/or crushing.
The EV Emitter is a crafting component for a few EV machines.
The EV Robot Arm is used for crafting a few EV machines, 2 of wihich are some of the most important for progression.
The EV Field Generator is used for making some possibly overpowered EV machines.
The Advanced Electromagnetic Separator III uses EV power to separate Pure Dusts that contain magnetic elements.
Tungsten is a strong metal, mainly used in alloys that are needed for progression. You can obtain it by Centrifuging Scheelite or Tungstate Dust.
Raw Carbon Fibers are an ingredient in making Circuit components, that you'll need later on.
The Nanocomponent Processing Unit is required for making all the Circuits in the nano line. It's made by adding a few Carbon Fibers and Glowstone to a regular CPU Wafer.
One of the Circuit Boards you are going to need in the future is the Epoxy one, so why not set up the automation for it now?
The Nanoprocessor is an Advanced Circuit.
The Nanoprocessor Assembly is an upgrade from the Nanoprocessor and is an extreme Circuit.
The Elite Nanocomputer is an upgrade from the Nanoprocessor Assembly and is an elite Circuit.
The Nanoprocessor Mainframe is an upgrade from the Elite Nanocomputer and is a master Circuit.
Now that your EBF has Kanthal Coils, you are able to make Glowstone Wafers, with which you can make 3 new Circuit components.
Polyphenylene Sulfide is a polymere that you'll be able to use as a substite for metal Foils in the recipes for EV+ Cables. It's made with Dichlorobenzene, Sodium Sulfide and Air or Oxygen.
Well, you have the Circuits, but this time you don't need anything new for making the Machine Hull. You can probably make it like right now.

Once you get 8 Neutronium Plates, you'll be able to make the MAX Machine Hull. 
 It's not really used for much, but it's a symbol of completing the pack, a different type of Trophy. It's just like a Trophy in real life, it takes a lot of time and dedication to get, but once you have it you can't use it for much. 
 I hope you had fun and stay tuned for my future packs.

-Pixel

betterquesting:10.name:8: Everything You Need To Know About: Sifting
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You can use Sieves with Meshes to obtain resources by sifting.

 Every Mesh has different outputs.

 You can sift in a 5x5 area of Sieves provided that they have the same Mesh.

 You can put inventories on top of Sieves to automatically collect the sifting outputs.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Everything You Need To Know About: Steam Machines
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Boilers auto-output Steam to adjacent machines or fluid containers on every side except the bottom.

 If the heat bar fills up and there is no Water in the Boiler, it will explode.

 For Steam machines to work continuosly, they need to exhaust Steam after every recipe. For that to be done, the side on which there's a black dot needs to have nothing placed on it.

 You can rotate the exhaust side with a Wrench.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Everything You Need To Know About: Electric Machines
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Generators output power on only one side, represented with a shiny white dot.

 Machines can auto-output items or fluids on the side represented with a hatch. You can choose whether to auto-output items or fluids by pressing the box-shaped buttons, with the grey one being items and the orange one being fluids.

 If a recipe that requires a lower voltage tier is done in a machine that's a higher tier, it will be overclocked, meaning 4 times more (scaling with the tier diffrence) EU/t is used, 2 times less time is needed for the recipe to be done and if there are byproducts, the chance of obtaining them doubles.

 Cables transfer power in the form of voltage and amps. An amp is a packet and the voltage is the size of the packet.

 If a machine has insufficient power, it will slowly lose progress. Once the bar is fully empty, you pretty much wasted the inputs.
No Description
With an MV Field Generator, you'll be able to make a Black Hole Unit and Tank, allowing you to store the 32-bit integer's worth of items and fluids.
If you don't want your Black Hole Units and Tanks taking up an entire block space, you can use a Black Hole Controller.

The Fission Reactor from NuclearCraft is a mildly shapeless multiblock structure consisting of Casings on the outside and Cells, for storing fuels, coolers, for decreasing heat, and Boron or Graphite Blocks, for increasing efficiency and heat, on the inside. You simply put a Fuel in and over time it will generate EU and RF and deplete the Fuel, which you'll then be able to thermal centrifuge in order to get some new materials.
From Depleted Thorium Fuel, you are able to obtain Lutetium.
From Depleted Uranium Fuel, you are able to obtain Tiny Clumps of Plutonium.
From Depleted Naquadah Fuel you are able to obtain Naquadria.
Radon is needed for making Quantum items. It can be obtained in an endless loop by having Plutonium Ingots go through a Chemical Reactor.
From Depleted MOX Fuel you can obtain Tiny Clumps of Plutonium 241.

Do you know which Circuit Board the Circuits after the ones that require the Fiber-Reinforced Epoxy Board require? They require the Multilayer Fiber-Reinforced Epoxy Board! Now, you might be a few hundred hours away from making them, but you should always be prepared, right?

Well, you made the Epoxy Board, but for the Circuits after the ones that require the Epoxy Board, you are going to need a Fiber-Reinforced Board, so why not automate that too? You can never be too prepared. While Fiber-Reinforced Board can be made with Carbon Fibers and Epoxy, it's more efficiently made with Glass Fibers and Epoxy. Glass Fibers are made wth Borosilicate Glass, which is made with Boron and Glass Dust. Boron can be obtained by centrifuging Borax or crushing Centrifuged Lepidolite Ore.

Reinforced Glass is more blast-proof than regular Glass and is used for making high tier machine. It's made with Advanced Alloy Plates, which are made by compressing Mixed Metal Plates. Mixed Metal Plates are made with different metal Plate combinations that yield different outputs. Why am I telling you this now? So you're prepared for the future!
The Distillation Tower is a multiblock structure consisting of 2-12 layers that distills items, but gives you multiple outputs, a different one from every layer.
The Diesel Engine is a multiblock version of the Diesel Generator. You can give it Oxygen and Lubricant to increase its fuel efficiency.
The Large Titanium Boiler can reach a higher temperature than the Steel one, but is even less fuel efficient.

The High Power IC is used for making a few high tier items and blocks related to storing a large amount of energy. Its Wafer is made with the one for a regular Power IC combined with Indium Gallium Phosphide. The Indium is obtained by reacting Indium Solution with Aluminium. The Indium Solution is made with Sulfuric Acid, Purified Spharelite and Purified Galena Ore.
The Electron Excitement Processor, also known as the  Advanced Electric Furnace IV, uses IV power to smelt items.

The Advanced Arc Furnace IV uses Oxygen and IV power to turn metal parts into Ingots and Nuggets. However, it comes at a cost. Rubber, Wood and plastics get turned into Ash, Copper gets turned into Annealed Copper and Iron gets turned into Wrough Iron.
The Advanced Alloy Smelter IV uses IV power to create alloys.
The Insane Voltage Transformer is able to turn EV power into IV power and vise versa.
The Insane Battery Buffer is able to store energy in Lapotron Energy Orbs. They're made with Lapotron Chips and Power ICs.
The Molecular Disintegrator E-4905, also known as the Advanced Electrolyzer IV, uses IV power to separate certain materials.
The Advanced Polarizer IV uses IV power to turn Iron, Steel and Nyodymium into their magnetic versions.
The IV Electric Motor is used in making most of the other IV machine components and itself is used in crafting many IV machines.
The IV Field Generator is used for making some possibly overpowered IV machines.
The IV Emitter is a crafting component for a few IV machines.
The IV Conveyor Module is simply used for crafting a few IV machines.
The IV Electric Pump is a common crafting components for IV machines that use fluids.
The IV Electric Piston is a crafting component for machines related to crushing and extracting.
The IV Robot Arm is used in crafting a few IV machines, 2 of which are the most important for progression.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Pump it up! Pump it up!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Advanced Pump IV uses IV power to collect Water every 12 ticks.

The last Circuit Board is the Wetware Life Support Circuit Board. It's made with Sterilized Growth Medium, which is heated Raw Growth Medium, which is a combination of Mince Meat, Sugar and Salt. Now, I know what you're thinking, and no, you can't eat it.
Kanthal is an alloy of Chrome, Iron and Aluminium. It's used for making some HV machines and Coils.
Nichrome is an alloy of Nickel and Chrome, used for some making some EV machines and Coils.
For making alloys needed for LuV machines, you are going to need to upgrade your Coils to Tungstensteel ones.
Niobium-Titanium is an alloy used in the recipes for most LuV machines. I'll let you guess what it's made from, it's a tricky one.
HSS-G is an alloy used in making LuV machine components. It's an alloy of Tungstensteel, Chrome and Vanadium.
For making HSS-E, HSS-S and other alloys, you are going to need to upgrade your Coils to HSS-G ones.
Naquadah is an alien metal used for making the strongest alloys and isotopes in the game.
For making Naquadah Alloy, you are going to need Naquadah Coils.
Yttrium Barium Cuprate is an alloy used in making a few LuV machines. What is it made from? Well, I'll let you guess. Hint: It's made from 3 elements.
Superconducter Wire is used in making many high tier items and machines.
Superconducter Coils allow you to make any Ingot in your Electric Blast Furnace.
No Description
The QBit Processing Unit is the next tier CPU. Its Wafer is made with a Nanocomponent Processing Unit's and either Gallium Arsenide and a Quantum Eye or Indium Gallium Phosphide and Radon.
The Advanced Aeembling Machine IV uses IV power to automatically craft items that take up to 4 different inputs. It's mainly used for Cables.
The Advanced Circuit Assembling Machine IV uses IV power to assemble Circuits.
The Blend-O-Matic 9001, also known as the Advanced Macerator IV, uses IV power to crush down items and double Ore outputs. It has 4 output slots.
The Advanced Brewery IV uses IV power to automatically brew Potions.
The Quantumprocessor is an extreme Circuit.
The Quantumprocessor Assembly is an upgrade from the Quantum Processor and it's an elite Circuit.
The Master Quantumcomputer is an upgrade from the Quantumprocessor Assembly and it a master Circuit.
The Quantumprocessor Mainframe is an upgrade from the Master Quantumcomputer and it's an ultimate Circuit.

The Assembly Line is a multiblock structure used for making IV+ crafting components. You can't easily tell what's what in JEI, so I'll tell you. On the bottom layer, in the middle you have ULV Input Buses with any tier Output Bus at the end, with Solid Steel Casing or Input Hatches next to them. On the second layer, you have Assembly Line Casings in the middle, with Reinforced Glass on the sides. On third layer you have Assembler Casings in the Middle with the Controller at the start, with Grate Machine Casings next to them. At the top you have Energy Hatches or Solid Steel Casings.
The Naquadah Reactor Mark 2 uses molten Naquadah to generate IV power.

The Naquadah Reactor Mark 1 uses molten Enriched Naquadah to generate EV power. It generates 15MEU per bucket, but to produce that much molten Enriched Naquadah you need about 8MEU, §lif no part of the process is overclocke§n§n§n§r§ld§0§r, meaning you only have a net gain of 7MEU. At the end of the day, it's much more than any other fuel.§r§r§f§r
The Molecular Cyclone, also known as the Turbo Centrifuge III, is used for separating certain items and fluids.
Argon is an element found in the Air in really small quantities and you probably won't be able to obtain by just centrifuging some Air. You'll first need to freeze the Air.
The Large Tungstensteel Boiler can reach the highest temperatures and mb/t out of all the Boilers, but it's the least fuel efficient.
Naquadah Wafers are the most efficient and also most expensive Wafers in the game. They also allow you to make SOCs and ASOCs, used for making some Circuits faster.
The Advanced Replicator IV uses IV power, Positive and Neutral Matter to replicate materials.
The Advanced Mass Fabricator IV uses IV power to separate items into Positive and Neutral Matter.
For getting into Fusion Reactors later on, you're going to need Iridium Alloy Plates. They're made by imploding a combination of Iridium, Advanced Alloy and Diamond Plates.

Before you get into Fusion Reactors, you are going to need Fusion Coils. They're made with master Circuits, MV Field Generators, Neutron Reflectors and Superconducter Coils. The Neutron Reflectors are the most expensive part, requiring an Iridium Alloy Plate, 3 Tungsten Carbide, an alloy of Tungsten and Carbon, 30 Beryllium and a whole lot of Tin Alloy. And that's only for one.
Before you can make some overpowered stuff, you are going to need to make a Neuroprocessor Board.
The Advanced Cluster Mill IV uses IV power to turn Plates into Foils.
The Advanced Wiremill IV uses IV power to turn Ingots into Wires.
The Advanced Mixer IV uses IV power to mix Dusts and fluids.
The Blaze Sweatshop T-6350, also known as the Advanced Thermal Centrifuge IV, uses IV power to centrifuge Crushed and Purified Ores.
The Advanced Microwave IV uses IV power to more efficiently cook food than the Electric Furnace. But only food!
The Advanced Forge Hammer IV uses IV power to crush down blocks and items.
The Advanced Autoclave IV uses IV power to turn gem Dusts into the corresponding gems.
The Advanced Bending Machine IV uses IV power to turn Ingots into Plates and Plates into Curved or Dense Plates.
The Repurposed Laundry Washer, also know as the Advanced Ore Washing Plant IV, is used for turning Crushed Ores into Purified ones.
The Advanced Sifting Machine IV uses IV power possibly give you a better version of a gem from your Crushed gem Ores.
The Advanced Precision Laser Engraver IV uses IV power and Lenses to engrave and etch certain items and blocks.
The Advanced Chemical Reactor IV uses IV power to force a reaction between items and/or fluids.
The Advanced Fluid Heater IV uses IV power to heat up certain fluids.
The Singularity Compressor, also known as the Advanced Compressor IV, uses IV power to compress various items, mainly into Blocks.
The Advanced Fermenter IV uses IV power to turn Biomass into Fermented Biomass.
The Advanced Fluid Solidifier IV uses IV power to cast fluids into usable items.
The Advanced Distillery IV uses IV power to distill certain fluids, giving only one output.
The Advanced Lathe IV uses IV power to turn Ingots and gems into Rods, Rods into Bolts and Bolts into Screws.
The Advanced Extruder IV uses IV power and Shapes to shape metals.
The Advanced Electromagnetic Separator IV uses IV power to separate Ores that contain magnetic elements.
The Advanced Canning Machine IV uses IV power to fill certain items with certain materials.
The Advanced Cutting Machine IV uses IV power and Water, Distilled Water or Lubricant to cut Blocks into Plates, as well as certain items into other items.
The Instant Fluid Canner uses IV power to automatically fill and empty fluid containers with fluids. Despite its name, it's not instant.
The Unboxinator uses IV power to uninsulate Cables and uncraft items in a 3x3.
The Boxinator uses IV power to automatically insulate  ULV and LV Wires and autocraft Tiny and Small Piles of Dusts into full Dusts.
The Advanced Chemical Bath IV uses IV power and certain fluids to purify Crushed Ores, undye blocks and make some other items.
The Vacuum Extractor uses IV power to extract certain materials from certain items.
The Advanced Fluid Extractor IV uses IV power to extract certain fluids from certain items.
The Basic Air Collector uses LV power to collect a bucket of Air every second.
The Advanced Air Collector II uses HV power to collect 4 buckets of Air every second.

You are finally able to get into nuclear fusion! All you are going to need is a Mark 1 Fusion Reactor. It's recommended that you use 16 Energy Input Hatches so your Computer's buffer is at max capacity, even if you don't plan on using all of them.
One of the first things you should make with your Mark 1 Fusion Reactor is Europium.
The Ludicrous Battery Buffer is able to store LuV power in Lapotron Energy Orb Clusters.
The Advanced Precision Laser Engraver V uses LuV power and Lenses to etch and engrave certain items.
The Advanced Autoclave V uses LuV power to turn gem Dusts into the corresponding gems as well as make a few other items from gems.

For making the top tier Circuits you are going to need Crystal Processing Units. They're made by engraving Engraved Crystal Chips, which are made with Raw Crystal Chips, Helium and Emerald or Olivine Plates in a Blast Furnace. The Engraved Crystal Chips are made in a Autoclave with Exquisite Olivines and Europium. They take some time to make and you only have a 10% chance of making them, but luckly you need only one and then you'll be able to cut your Crystal Processing Units to make more.
The LuV Electric Motor is used for making most of the other machine components as well as a few machines.
The Crystalprocessor is an extreme Circuit.
The Crystalprocessor Assembly is an upgrade from the Crystalprocessor and it's a master Circuit.
The Advanced Circuit Assembling Machine V uses LuV power to assemble Circuits.
The LuV Electric Pump is used for crafting most machines that use fluids in their recipes.
The Ultimate Crystalcomputer is an upgrade from the Crystal Processor Assembly and it's an ultimate Circuit.
The Crystalprocessor Mainframe is an upgrade from the Ultimate Crystalcomputer and it's a super Circuit.
No Description

The LuV Field Generator is used for making some possibly overpowered LuV machines.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Everything You Need To Know About: Quests
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Many quests have multiple tasks that you switch between using the arrows next to the detect button.

 Quests that have rounded square icons are needed for progressing to higher tiers, while the ones with circular icons are mainly quality of life quests.

 In this pack you don't get quest rewards, but you do get Trophies for major milestones.

 Items in your inventory are checked every 3 seconds, so wait at least 3s to make sure something is detected before using it up.

 If you complete a quest before it's unlocked, you'll need to press the detect button.

 Fluids tasks require you to have all fluids in your inventory at the same time.

 Ages related to GregTech have positive numbers and ages related to other mods have negative nubers.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Everything You Need To Know About: Multiblocks
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Multiblocks can share walls, but not Hatches/Buses.

 You can check the uses or recipes of most multiblock Controllers to see examples for the multiblocks' structures.

 The Coke Oven and Primitive Blast Furnace can have items inputted/outputted through the Controller.

 Besides for the Assembly Line and Fusion Reactor, all multiblocks that use Hatches can use any tier of Hatch.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Everything You Need To Know About: Pressure
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Pressure evens out through the system.

 Pressure can leak through an unconnected Tube.

 Most machines have a pressure limit above which they'll have a chance to explode.

 You can use certain items to save your pressure system from explosions.

With an Apiary you'll be able to start breeding your Bees and getting different products from them.

As you could have guessed, the Peat-Fired Engine uses peat to generate RF.

You can make a multiblock Farm that uses RF, Water, Dirt and Fertilizer to auomatically plant and harvest crops and trees. It needs to be at least a 3x4x3 and it needs to have a platform to place Dirt on the top layer.
The Flexible Casing is the base for all Automatic Farm blocks.

Monastic Bees require an Ancient Gold Coin. It can be obtained via the Amadron.
In order to obtain Tropical Bees you are going to need Vines. Vines can be obtained from large jungle trees.
The most common drop from Bees is Honey Combs. They can be centrifuged into Honey Drops.
Some Bees can hurt you when you're near them. To protect yourself, with the Silk gotten from Tropical Bees, you can make yourself and Apiarist's set.
The Analyzer uses Honey and Dew Drops to analyze Bees and show you their stats.

You can analyzer regular vanilla Saplings to turn them into Forestry version and then grow them near your Apiaries. Over time, they'll start getting cross-bred. To obtain the Saplings of the new trees, you can use a Grafter.

Drums
-Store 4 times the amount of fluid the corresponding Tanks do
-You can't see the fluid in them
-They take 2-4 more Ingots than Tanks, but no Glass

Crates
-Store 1.5-2 times the amount of different items the corresponding Chests do
-They take up a whole block space
-They limit JEI usage in Automatic
-They take about the same amount of materials as Chests

For them to function, you're going to need to place them before placing the Controller.

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
GT tools are the only tools you can make in this pack.

 Tools use the pre-1.9 combat system, so you don't have to wait before attacking.
